Exercise 11 — Full Git workflow (combined)

This covers the last long list (configure user, clone, modify README, status, stage, commit,
push, branch, git log).
Follow these steps:
1. Configure your Git user information
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your-email@example.com"
2. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YourUser/repository.git
cd repository
3. Open README.txt and make a minor change
● Edit README.txt in any text editor and add your name under Contributors.
Contributors:
- Your Name
4. Check the status of your repository
git status
# Expected: modified: README.txt
5. Stage the changes you made to README.txt
git add README.txt
6. Commit your changes
git commit -m "Add my name to contributors list"
7. Push your changes to the remote repository
git push origin main
# or if on a branch:
git push -u origin feature/add-my-name
8. Create and switch to a new branch called feature/add-my-name
git checkout -b feature/add-my-name
# make changes, then:
git add .
git commit -m "Add my name on branch"
git push -u origin feature/add-my-name
9. Demonstrate git log command
git log --oneline --decorate --graph --all